    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I the Emacs world, `ControlG` is used for cancelling stuff. Reverse search, selection, etc...\n- `Control-Space` (or `control-@` for terminals that don't know `control-space`): enter selection mode.\n- `ControlW`: cut\n- `Meta-W`: copy\n- `ControlY`: paste\n- `ControlG`: cancel\n\nFYI:\n- `ControlX`: Go to the start/end of a given line.\n- `ControlC` Abort input\n- `ControlV` Scroll down.\n\nMore info: https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_node/emacs/Clipboard.html\nPrompt-toolkit does not yet have a \"kill-ring\" like Emacs, `M-y` is not yet implemented.\n"
  },
