    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "```\nAlso we might want selection mode to not be triggerable when the buffer is empty.\n```\n\nThat's a good suggestion. I'll fix that.\n\nFixed: https://github.com/jonathanslenders/python-prompt-toolkit/commit/a9877111ed3c8ab1e2988e2a2432d6929ae3b3ec\n\nEdit:\n\n```\nCtrlC DOes exit the mode, but does not immediately change the cursor blinking mode which is confusing.\n```\n\nEdit2: I thought this was a bug, but it's not. There is an Emacs binding `ControlC >` and `ControlC <` which indents/unindents the selected region. Because of that, the first `ControlC` doesn't do anything yet, because it doesn't know yet what will follow.\n\nIf you want `ControlC` to take effect immediately, but because of that disable the indentation key bindings. Add the following:\n\n``` python\n@handle(Keys.ControlC, eager=True, filter=HasSelection())\ndef _(event):\n    event.current_buffer.exit_selection()\n```\n"
